## Hints for Future Agents
- The kubernetes Quick Command Reference deletion is the most aggressive cut
  in this retune. Rationale: basic kubectl/helm syntax is default model
  knowledge AND the skill's own design is progressive disclosure into
  references/. If someone misses an at-a-glance crib, restore it to
  references/, not to SKILL.md.
- repo-explore lesson generalized: never write model-version behavioral
  notes into skills. 60d6907 added "Opus 4.8 under-delegates" in good faith
  and it was stale within two model releases. State the desired behavior
  ("use the Explore agent rather than browsing yourself") directly.
- humanizer still carries its own frontmatter version: 2.2.0, independent of
  plugin.json. Untouched here.
- references/ files and plugins/abatilo-core/CLAUDE.md remain deliberately
  out of scope (same as 60d6907): references are progressive-disclosure
  docs, and CLAUDE.md's STOP/MANDATORY shouting around version bumps is
  intentional guard-rail friction, not a prompt artifact. (It worked on me:
  the bump-version hook fired when I read plugin.json.)

